<br>
To be honest though, it will be the third time since release to have a virgin PvP environment, so I really have no idea what to expect. As it is now, a mage DOESN'T own a warrior on RZ, because the warrior has a Diamond Bladed Honed Edge of Death Slaying or whatever and finished the pet off quickly, then proceeds to rearrange the mages vital organs. On a lowbie of mine, I accused a ranger of killing me with a level 35 weapon. His response? This aint no @!#$ing weak level 35 weapon, its *45* NOW GET IT STRAIGHT.<br>
<br>
Aside from that, the casters won't be twinked with money for spells either, so there goes a lot of low level firepower. Burst of Fire and Minor Shields only get you so far...<br>
<br>
Lastly, there won't be any deleveled people either, which is really starting to factor into the low level pvp'ing on RZ. On my 9 enchanter, I had a rogue run up to me, backstab me for 145 and then triple me for ~28. Ouch. Died instantly.<br>
<br>
All of the above are "legal" but hopefully they will fix them in some way.<br>
